```

ğŸ‘‰ Forces a restart **without shutting down services cleanly** â†’ risky if unsaved work.

---

### 3. Reboot with scheduling

Linux prefers `shutdown` for scheduling:

```bash
sudo shutdown -r +10
```

ğŸ‘‰ Restarts system in 10 minutes.

---

### 4. Reboot with message

```bash
sudo shutdown -r now "System will reboot for updates"
```

ğŸ‘‰ Sends message to all logged-in users before restarting.

---

## ğŸ“Œ Related Commands

| Command       | Purpose                                   |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `poweroff`    | Turns off the system                      |
| `halt`        | Stops all processes but may not power off |
| `shutdown -r` | Schedule or immediately reboot            |
| `reboot`      | Immediate restart                         |

